data.title: Doraemon
data.synopsis: Doraemon is cat shaped robot from the future traveling all the way back to the 20th century in order to help Nobi Nobita, a lazy kid with nothing really going for him. Nobi is bad at sports, his grades are terrible, he can't even win a match of rock-paper-scissors. Doraemon has a hard task ahead of him but he is well prepared with a huge arsenal of the most inventive and funny gadgets available. The problem is he's not the most competent robot cat helper out there either and the pair gets in constant trouble because of it. Thus begins one of the most interesting friendships ever to appear in a manga series.
data.background: Doraemon has been published in English by Shogakukan Asia since August 27, 2014 and digitally by Shogakukan since Nov 22, 2013.

data.title: Daichouhen Doraemon
data.synopsis: "Doraemon" is a series about a robotic cat named Doraemon, who travels back in time from the 22nd century to help a schoolboy named Nobita Nobi. Aside from the normal manga books, their great adventures to different places are specially described in Doraemon Long Stories books. (Source: MU)
data.background: The original author, Fujiko F Fujio, died while working on the 17th volume of the series. The rest was continued by his corporation, Fujiko F. Fujio Producton.

titles.title: ドラベース ドラえもん超野球〈スーパーベースボール〉外伝

data.title: Dorabase: Doraemon Super Baseball Gaiden
data.title_japanese: ドラベース ドラえもん超野球〈スーパーベースボール〉外伝
data.synopsis: Dorabase takes place in Tokyo in the 22nd century. The protagonist of the story is Kuroemon, a cat robot of the same type as Doraemon and the captain and team manager of the baseball team Edogawa Doras. The manga focuses on the stories of the Edogawa Doras, as it faces countless adversaries and grows from a team unable to win even a single game to a world class amateur baseball team. The rules for baseball remain largely unchanged in the 22nd century, with the notable exception that three designated secret gadgets from the main Doraemon series can be used in each game. (Source: Wikipedia)

titles.title: ドラえもんゲームコミック ザ☆ドラえもんズ

data.title: Doraemon Game Comic: The☆Doraemons
data.title_japanese: ドラえもんゲームコミック ザ☆ドラえもんズ
data.synopsis: A spin-off of the long-running Doraemon manga, The Doraemons follows the adventures of the six different Doraemon that first appeared in the 3DO game, Doraemon-Legend of Friendship, The Doraemon. The Doraemons, or Dora Dora Seven (DD7), is a kind of an old boys' association of the Robot School which Doraemon attended. All the seven male members are cat-like robots of the same type, enjoy dorayaki, but usually add their own preferred seasoning. They have rock-hard heads they can use as a weapons, or to break out of prison (among other things), but this is even more enhanced in Doraemon, since he has no other special weapons, and has no ears or hat to get in the way when using this mode of attack. The gadget that can connect them is Friendship Telecard. They can call each other with the card everywhere and every time when one or more members are facing problems. (Source: Wikipedia)

data.title: The☆Doraemons Special
data.title_japanese: ザ☆ドラえもんズスペシャル
data.synopsis: Another journey of The Doraemons. This series have a very major difference with Nobita's frequent participation in most of the Doraemons' adventures, instead of the only focus on the Doraemons. However, other recurring characters from the main series (Shizuka, etc.) and human partners of other DD7 members don't have too much focus as same as Nobita. The adventures mostly appear in many different eras rather than 22nd century, and some of the character settings have slight differences from the original version by Tanaka. (Source: Wikipedia)

data.title: Demon Busters: Ecchi na Ecchi na Demon Taiji
data.title_japanese: デーモンバスターズ ～えっちなえっちなデーモン退治～
data.synopsis: Kou is a member of the public morals committee at Moriyaji Gakuen, along with his childhood friend Ai and kouhai Karen. One day while he was making the rounds after school, he was attacked by a weird being. He was frozen in fear and could not evade its attack, but he was saved by two girls, Konoka and Lizera. They were ‘daemon busters’ who fight against daemons borne from the lust and cravings of humans. They told him that he was a kyuumashi who could absorb the desires that create daemons, and they asked for his help since his special ability makes their battles much easier. When he uses his ability, it causes him to be able to see girls naked and also makes them horny. If the daemons aren’t defeated, then their lust will cause the whole school to become an orgy. As part of the public morals committee, he can’t let that happen! (Source: Hau~ Omochikaeri!)

data.synopsis: I returned to Earth after hunting demons in the otherworld for three hundred years. But I did not return alone. (Source: Naver Corporation, translated)
data.background: The Knight King Who Returned with a God faced immediate controversy due to the art's purported use of AI and strong resemblance to the series Mushoku Tensei. Blueline Studio, the studio which produced the series, made a statement admitting to the use of AI retouching, and reuploaded the chapters without the AI retouching.

titles.title: The Return of Elena the Knight
The Return of Elena the Knight

data.title: The Return of Elena the Knight
data.title_english: The Return of Elena the Knight
data.synopsis: Elena Blaise grew up as a count's daughter in a royalist household backing Crown Prince Carlisle. The prince's sudden assassination makes way for the Anti-King Paveluc, who annihilates House Blaise overnight. As the sole survivor, Elena trains as a knight to avenge her family. When she finally faces off with Paveluc, a deadly blow not only knocks her unconscious but also catapults her into the past! Elena wakes up one year before the fall of House Blaise. Determined to protect her kin, she rushes to save Crown Prince Carlisle, asking for his hand in marriage and offering her services as his knight. Bewildered as he is, Carlisle takes the bait. The future now lies in the hands of his fiancée fighting on his behalf! (Source: Tappytoon)
data.background: The Return of Elena the Knight was published digitally in English by Tappytoon from September 7, 2021 to May 3, 2023.

titles.title: Han Dae Sung Returned From Hell

data.title: Returned From Hell
title_synonyms: Han Dae Sung Returned From Hell
data.synopsis: One day, middle school student Daesung Han suddenly falls into hell, which had a game-like system. After fighting to survive for 80 years, he finally defeats the Demon God, and a message pops up asking "Would You Like to Return to Earth?" He accepts, and wakes up in a hospital bed, having been in a vegetative state ever since he fell into hell. Only 10 years had passed on Earth, and during that time, wormholes called Gates teeming with monsters from another dimension began appearing, which are dealt with by professionals known as Hunters. Daesung struggles with the harsh reality of losing all the power he'd gained in those 80 years, when suddenly a quest pop-up from hell appears.

titles.title: Dragon Knights Gaiden: One Day, Another Day
ドラゴン騎士団外伝ワンデイ・アナザーデイ

data.title: Dragon Knights Gaiden: One Day, Another Day
data.title_japanese: ドラゴン騎士団外伝ワンデイ・アナザーデイ
data.synopsis: A collection of Dragon Knights one shots and sidestories originally published in WINGS magazine. The summaries below are taken from DK Sanctuary Title Story: One Day, Another Day Summary: Set before the end of the series, it's basically a side story of a day in the Dragon Castle, kind of in Zoma's perspective. Title: Juuji ni Hikaru Hoshi Summary: Takes place before the events of the actual series. This is a back story that shows how Lykouleon and Raselane met, introducing Lykouleon's uncle, Fieruto. Title: Mamono no Mori no Kioku Summary: Another backstory that delves a little bit more into the relationship between Bierrez and Cesia before the series started. It also shows how Nadil became the demon lord. Title: Happiest Children Summary: This actually has three little side stories in it. The first one is about Rune's dream about everyone dressed in drag, the second is about a little adventure that the three dragons go on, and then the third is like a day in the life of Alfeegi, Ri-ma, and Duma. Title: Crescendo Summary: Backstory about how Lykouleon and Kaistern met and how Kaistern then became the Blue Dragon Officer. Title: CONFESSION - Thats Summary: This is basically the backstory of Thatz and how he knew about Rath's little secret. Title: CONFESSION - Rath Summary: The final gaiden published by Ohkami through WINGS. Basically telling a lot about Rath, particularly his relationship with Kaistern.
